<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="570" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="5" pageNumber="570">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,713,1615]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="570">
1. Vertex very smooth and almost impunctate (fig. 1A, C, F in 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[812,985,713,735]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="3 - 7" refId="ref15853" refString="Shinohara, A. (2019 a) Konowia harai n. sp. (Hymenoptera, Xiphydriidae) from Japan. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology, 25, 3 - 7." type="journal article" year="2019">Shinohara, 2019a</bibRefCitation>
); female antenna largely whitish and abdomen with lateral white spots (fig. 1A, B, D, F in 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[651,823,742,764]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="3 - 7" refId="ref15853" refString="Shinohara, A. (2019 a) Konowia harai n. sp. (Hymenoptera, Xiphydriidae) from Japan. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology, 25, 3 - 7." type="journal article" year="2019">Shinohara, 2019a</bibRefCitation>
); male with tufts of long golden hairs on abdominal sterna (fig. 1C in 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[285,457,772,794]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" pagination="3 - 7" refId="ref15853" refString="Shinohara, A. (2019 a) Konowia harai n. sp. (Hymenoptera, Xiphydriidae) from Japan. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology, 25, 3 - 7." type="journal article" year="2019">Shinohara, 2019a</bibRefCitation>
)... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara &amp; Hara" authorityYear="2021" box="[490,606,772,793]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphydriidae" genus="Monoxiphia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[490,606,772,793]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Monoxiphia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
............................................................. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="2019" box="[1352,1436,772,793]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphydriidae" genus="Monoxiphia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="harai">
<emphasis box="[1352,1436,772,793]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">M. harai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,713,1615]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="570">
– Vertex largely covered with coarse surface microsculpture, or rather smooth but partly coriaceous with sparce large punctures (
<figureCitation box="[233,290,830,852]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1649,1673]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,187,1620]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1435,181,1625]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Heads, females, dorsal (A–C, G–J) and dorsolateral (D–F, J–L) view. --- A, D, K. betulae, Altenburg, Germany; B, E, K. betulae, Akaigawa, Hokkaido, holotype of Platyxiphydria nishijimai; C, F, K. kojimai, Yakumo, Hokkaido; G, J, K. kojimai, Yumine, Honshu, holotype; H, K, K. megapolitana, Łódż, Poland; I, L, K. yasumatsui, Nikko, Honshu." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4491276" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4491276/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
); female with antenna and abdomen black (
<figureCitation box="[711,768,830,852]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1890,1914]" captionTargetBox="[207,1381,539,1860]" captionTargetId="figure-194@7.[202,1385,534,1864]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 1. Females (A–F) and males (G–I). --- A, K. betulae, Akaigawa, Hokkaido, holotype of Platyxiphydria nishijimai; B, K. betulae, Nukabira-ko, Hokkaido; C, K. kojimai, Yumine, Honshu, holotype; D, K. kojimai, Yakumo, Hokkaido; E, K. megapolitana, Łódż, Poland; F, K. yasumatsui, Nikko, Honshu; G, K. betulae, Memuro-dake, Hokkaido; H, K. kojimai, Asahidakeonsen, Hokkaido; I, K. yasumatsui, Sobo-sancho, Kyushu." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4491272" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4491272/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Figs 1</figureCitation>
A–F, 2); male without tufts of long golden hairs on abdominal sterna. … 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brauns" authorityYear="1884" box="[256,343,860,881]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphydriidae" genus="Konowia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[256,343,860,881]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Konowia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
…....................................................................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="5" pageNumber="570">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,713,1615]" box="[151,1436,889,911]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,889,911]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">2. Female...........................................................................................… 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,713,1615]" box="[151,1436,918,940]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,918,940]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">– Male. …............................................................................................ 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="5" pageNumber="570">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,713,1615]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="570">
3. Antenna thick, with flagellomere 2 about 1.5–1.9× longer than broad (
<figureCitation box="[917,975,948,970]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1789,1813]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,188,1758]" captionTargetId="figure-20@12.[164,1423,181,1765]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 4. Antennae, K. betulae (A–J), K. kojimai (K–O), K. megapolitana (P, Q) and K. yasumatsui (R–U), females (A–I, K–N, P–T) and males (J, O, U). --- A, Altenburg, Germany; B, Mirugam, Korea; C, Nukabira-ko, Hokkaido; D, Horoshika-toge, Hokkaido; E, Nissho-toge, Hokkaido; F, Izumisawa, Hokkaido; G, Akaigawa, Hokkaido, holotype of Platyxiphydria nishijimai; H, same specimen as A, pedicel and base of flagellum; I, same specimen as B, pedicel and base of flagellum; J, Memuro-dake, Hokkaido; K, Nissho-toge, Hokkaido; L, Yakumo, Hokkaido; M, Yumine, Honshu, holotype; N, same specimen as L, pedicel and base of flagellum; O, Asahidake-onsen, Hokkaido; P, Łódż, Poland; Q, same specimen as P, pedicel and base of flagellum; R, Nikko, Honshu; S, Omogokei, Shikoku; T, same specimen as R, pedicel and base of flagellum; U, Sobo-sancho, Kyushu." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4491280" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4491280/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
A–J, R–U); forewing with crossvein 2r-m basal to crossvein 2m-cu on vein M and vein 1A narrowly separated from or shortly fused with 2A+3A (
<figureCitation box="[1175,1306,977,999]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1890,1914]" captionTargetBox="[207,1381,539,1860]" captionTargetId="figure-194@7.[202,1385,534,1864]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 1. Females (A–F) and males (G–I). --- A, K. betulae, Akaigawa, Hokkaido, holotype of Platyxiphydria nishijimai; B, K. betulae, Nukabira-ko, Hokkaido; C, K. kojimai, Yumine, Honshu, holotype; D, K. kojimai, Yakumo, Hokkaido; E, K. megapolitana, Łódż, Poland; F, K. yasumatsui, Nikko, Honshu; G, K. betulae, Memuro-dake, Hokkaido; H, K. kojimai, Asahidakeonsen, Hokkaido; I, K. yasumatsui, Sobo-sancho, Kyushu." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4491272" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4491272/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Figs 1A, B, F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1316,1376,977,999]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[183,1406,185,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@15.[178,1410,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 6. Wings, females (A–C), hind legs, males (D, E) and tarsal claws, K. yasumatsui (F–K), female, Nikko, Honshu (F–H) and male, Sobo-sancho, Kyushu (I–K). --- A, K. betulae, Horoshika-toge, Hokkaido; B, K. kojimai, Yumine, Honshu, holotype; C, K. yasumatsui, Omogokei, Shikoku; D, K. betulae, Memuro-dake, Hokkaido; E, K. kojimai, Horoshika-toge, Hokkaido; F, I, Fore legs; G, J, mid legs; H, K, hind legs." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4491284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4491284/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">6A, C</figureCitation>
); hind tarsomere 1 long, about 1.1–1.3× length of tarsomeres 2–4 combined (
<figureCitation box="[901,979,1006,1028]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[183,1406,185,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@15.[178,1410,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 6. Wings, females (A–C), hind legs, males (D, E) and tarsal claws, K. yasumatsui (F–K), female, Nikko, Honshu (F–H) and male, Sobo-sancho, Kyushu (I–K). --- A, K. betulae, Horoshika-toge, Hokkaido; B, K. kojimai, Yumine, Honshu, holotype; C, K. yasumatsui, Omogokei, Shikoku; D, K. betulae, Memuro-dake, Hokkaido; E, K. kojimai, Horoshika-toge, Hokkaido; F, I, Fore legs; G, J, mid legs; H, K, hind legs." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4491284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4491284/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
); valvula 3 (apical sheath) long, about 1.0–1.1× length of valvifer 2 (basal sheath) (
<figureCitation box="[562,624,1036,1058]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1265,1289]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,188,1235]" captionTargetId="figure-20@16.[151,1435,181,1241]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 7. Ovipositor sheaths, K. betulae, lateral view. --- A, Altenburg, Germany; B, Mirugam, Korea; C, Akaigawa, Hokkaido, holotype of Platyxiphydria nishijimai; D, Nukabira-ko, Hokkaido; E, Izumisawa, Hokkaido; F, Nissho-toge, Hokkaido." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4491286" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4491286/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">
Figs 
<geoCoordinate box="[610,624,1036,1057]" degrees="7, 8" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="5" pageNumber="570" precision="5555" value="7.8">7</geoCoordinate>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[640,695,1036,1057]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1262,1286]" captionTargetBox="[209,1380,189,1233]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[201,1386,181,1238]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ovipositor sheaths, K. kojimai (A–C), K. megapolitana (D) and K. yasumatsui (E, F), lateral view. --- A, Nissho-toge, Hokkaido; B, Yakumo, Hokkaido; C, Yumine, Honshu, holotype; D, Łódż, Poland; E, Nikko, Honshu; F, Omogokei, Shikoku." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4491288" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4491288/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">8E, F</figureCitation>
)............................................................ 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,713,1615]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="570">
– Antenna thin, with flagellomere 2 about 2.7–4.4× longer than broad (
<figureCitation box="[893,950,1065,1087]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1789,1813]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,188,1758]" captionTargetId="figure-20@12.[164,1423,181,1765]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 4. Antennae, K. betulae (A–J), K. kojimai (K–O), K. megapolitana (P, Q) and K. yasumatsui (R–U), females (A–I, K–N, P–T) and males (J, O, U). --- A, Altenburg, Germany; B, Mirugam, Korea; C, Nukabira-ko, Hokkaido; D, Horoshika-toge, Hokkaido; E, Nissho-toge, Hokkaido; F, Izumisawa, Hokkaido; G, Akaigawa, Hokkaido, holotype of Platyxiphydria nishijimai; H, same specimen as A, pedicel and base of flagellum; I, same specimen as B, pedicel and base of flagellum; J, Memuro-dake, Hokkaido; K, Nissho-toge, Hokkaido; L, Yakumo, Hokkaido; M, Yumine, Honshu, holotype; N, same specimen as L, pedicel and base of flagellum; O, Asahidake-onsen, Hokkaido; P, Łódż, Poland; Q, same specimen as P, pedicel and base of flagellum; R, Nikko, Honshu; S, Omogokei, Shikoku; T, same specimen as R, pedicel and base of flagellum; U, Sobo-sancho, Kyushu." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4491280" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4491280/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
K–Q); forewing with crossvein 2r-m usually interstitial with crossvein 2m-cu and vein 1A fused with 2A+3A for a long distance (
<figureCitation box="[992,1049,1094,1116]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1890,1914]" captionTargetBox="[207,1381,539,1860]" captionTargetId="figure-194@7.[202,1385,534,1864]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 1. Females (A–F) and males (G–I). --- A, K. betulae, Akaigawa, Hokkaido, holotype of Platyxiphydria nishijimai; B, K. betulae, Nukabira-ko, Hokkaido; C, K. kojimai, Yumine, Honshu, holotype; D, K. kojimai, Yakumo, Hokkaido; E, K. megapolitana, Łódż, Poland; F, K. yasumatsui, Nikko, Honshu; G, K. betulae, Memuro-dake, Hokkaido; H, K. kojimai, Asahidakeonsen, Hokkaido; I, K. yasumatsui, Sobo-sancho, Kyushu." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4491272" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4491272/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Figs 1</figureCitation>
C–E, 6B); hind tarsomere 1 short, about 1.0× length of tarsomeres 2–4 combined (
<figureCitation box="[627,702,1124,1146]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[183,1406,185,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@15.[178,1410,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 6. Wings, females (A–C), hind legs, males (D, E) and tarsal claws, K. yasumatsui (F–K), female, Nikko, Honshu (F–H) and male, Sobo-sancho, Kyushu (I–K). --- A, K. betulae, Horoshika-toge, Hokkaido; B, K. kojimai, Yumine, Honshu, holotype; C, K. yasumatsui, Omogokei, Shikoku; D, K. betulae, Memuro-dake, Hokkaido; E, K. kojimai, Horoshika-toge, Hokkaido; F, I, Fore legs; G, J, mid legs; H, K, hind legs." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4491284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4491284/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Fig. 6E</figureCitation>
); valvula 3 short, about 0.8–1.0× length of valvifer 2 (
<figureCitation box="[1223,1278,1124,1146]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1262,1286]" captionTargetBox="[209,1380,189,1233]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[201,1386,181,1238]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 8. Ovipositor sheaths, K. kojimai (A–C), K. megapolitana (D) and K. yasumatsui (E, F), lateral view. --- A, Nissho-toge, Hokkaido; B, Yakumo, Hokkaido; C, Yumine, Honshu, holotype; D, Łódż, Poland; E, Nikko, Honshu; F, Omogokei, Shikoku." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4491288" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4491288/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
A–D)....... 5
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="5" pageNumber="570">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,713,1615]" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="570">
4. Mesoscutellum with distinct microsculpture, mat all over (
<figureCitation box="[795,903,1153,1175]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1620,1644]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,425,1591]" captionTargetId="figure-149@14.[151,1435,417,1597]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 5. Thoraces, showing surface microsculpture of mesoscutellum, females, dorsal (A–C) and dorsolateral (D–F) view. --- A, D, K. betulae, Akaigawa, Hokkaido, holotype of Platyxiphydria nishijimai; B, E, K. kojimai, Yakumo, Hokkaido; C, F, K. yasumatsui, Nikko, Honshu." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4491282" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4491282/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="570">Fig. 5A, D</figureCitation>
